                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_ændavyn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ændavyn</orth><form type="participle"><orth>ændævd</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ændavun</orth><form type="participle"><orth>ændavd</orth></form></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>греть</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>to warm</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>давать себя чувствовать</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>to affect smb.</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>трогать</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>to touch</q></abv:tr></sense></sense><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>xūr dardmæ ændavy</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>солнце греет на далекое расстояние</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>the sun heats for a great distance</q></abv:tr></abv:example><abv:example><quote>xūr tyngdær ærændævta, mīt hæjttæj tadī</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>солнце сильнее пригрело, снег бурно таял</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>the sun warmed up more, the snow was rapidly melting</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_F."/><biblScope>1957 III 30</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>wazal ændagddær ændavuj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>холод сильнее дает себя чувствовать</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>it s getting colder here</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/><biblScope>78</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>dæ nyxæstæ mæ ne ʽndavync</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>твои слова меня не трогают</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>your words don’t touch me</q></abv:tr></abv:example><abv:example><quote>fælladæj sæ wajtaǧd tarf fynæj ærændævta</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>усталых, их сразу охватил глубокий сон</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>as they were tired, they immediately fell asleep</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>II 144</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из %iæm-tavyn%i, сращение преверба %iæm-%i с глаголом <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tavyn"/> ˈгретьˈ, бытующим и самостоятельно. Для сращения %iæm-tav-%i (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>ham-tap-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>sam-tap-</w></mentioned>) ср. <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/> <w>andaw</w> <gloss><q>жар</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘лихорадка’. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æntæf"/> ˈжараˈ, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæfsæg"/> ˈлихорадкаˈ, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tavyn"/> ˈгретьˈ, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæfsyn"/> ˈсогреватьсяˈ, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tævd"/> ˈгорячийˈ, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ændævyn"/> ˈкоченетьˈ.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From %iæm-tavyn%i, the fusion of the preverb %iæm-%i with the verb <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tavyn"/> ‘to heat’, which is used independently as well. For the fusion%i æm-tav-%i (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/> <w>ham-tap-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>sam-tap-</w></mentioned>) cf. <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/> <w>andaw</w> <gloss><q>fever</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æntæf"/> ˈheatˈ, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæfsæg"/> ˈfeverˈ, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tavyn"/> ˈto heatˈ, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæfsyn"/> ˈto get warmˈ, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tævd"/> ˈhotˈ, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ændævyn"/> ˈto stiffenˈ</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>